Son of [[Sai of Wa|Sai]] and brother of [[Bu of Wa|Bu]], one of the ''[[Five kings of Wa|Kings of Wa]]''. Some have compared him to the 20th [[Emperor Ankō]], others to [[Ichinobe no Oshiwa|Prince Ichibe Oshiwa]],<ref>"Hanzoku Wa-jin Kō" (漢籍和人考), first published by [[Kan Masatomo]] in 1892 (Meiji 25, [[:en:1892|1892]]). </ref> or [[Prince Kinashi no Karu|Kinashi no Karu]].<ref>"Ancient Japanese History" by [[Kunitake Kume]], first published in 1907 ([[:en:1907|1907]]). </ref>
